review_blob: A stout aroma at first that  vanishes quickly, a dark colour with a tan head that becames almost nothing after a short time. Really sour taste and palate, I would say this particular one was infected or something but reading the rest of the comments it must be the "complexity" they are talking about in the label.. A badly done dry stout or simply a bad beer.

An interesting design of the label to begin with. As far as the aroma grassy, maybe leaves is some way. A golden liquid with a generos white head that goes down slowly. Really bitter with a medium body, a standing carbonation with a bitter finish and a thin texture. Overall an interesting concept well realized, nothing too fancy but nice.

Zero aroma whatsoever, probably because of the lack of carbonation,nothing impressive or meaningful when tasting, just a light bitterness but disappears too soon for me. Light body with a flat carbonation and a minimal, to say something, head over a cloudy amber beer. From where I am standing doenst worth the try.

A rich citruousy aroma, banana even.. A generous white head when pouring that disappears in a short time leaving a cloudy golden beer. A fresh sensation tasting it, fruity flavour at first that fastly becames a light bitterness. Really light body and thin texture, a lot of carbonation at first than comes less  after a while. Overall a good witbier, with some defects but nothing serious.

Nice dark amber color, clear  with just the minimal head on top after a little bit. Some alcoholic aroma, kind of expected from a 10 belgian strong ale, remembering distilled spirits, maybe herbs and grass too. Light sweet and bitterness, mixed perfectly. Soft carbonation but at the first impression looks more than it really is, medium to full body with a clear bitter finish. Overall an excellent beer, really well balanced and enjoyable at any time.

The label itself its a beauty, the drawing of a sort of squid its funny with all the details added. When pouring it creates a good tanned head that disappears into a thin layer. Nice aroma, fresh and typical of a porter. Notes of chocolate malt, bitter aftertaste. Medium body and overall a well done porter with a Left Hand interpretation.

Nice stout, little more carbonated than usually a stout but just when pouring, with a tanned head that fastly disappears. Taste with clear notes of coffee and toasted cereals, with almost no aftertaste, just a little bitterness. Fresh aroma for a stout and above a medium body. Really nice overall.

A nice looking beer, from the deScription, as always very peculiar, to the moment of pouring the beer. An alcoholic aroma mixed with notes of jerez, really peculiar and strong. The taste is a enjoyable, kinda sweet but at the time bitter, experience, a lot of notes remembering the alcohol that contents. The palate is the best moment, chocolate, coffee, roast cereal...just a explosion after the beer goes down the throat. Even with that amount of alcohol,a very drinkable beer, not for everyday obviously, but still as strong as it may appear.

Typical Ale aroma from the beginning to the end, slighty spicy notes when pouring. A beautiful red clear appearance with a tan color head on top. Medium taste, obviosly bitter than stands in the mouth for a while giving that thin texture on the tongue mixed with a complex body of a pretty well done ale. Overall a nice red ale to enjoy without a doubt, not too fancy but not boring at all.
